HEADWORD: Ululation
<hw>Ul`u*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ululatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>A howling, as of a dog or wolf; a
wailing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He may fright others with his <qex>ululation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wither.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ulva</ent>⟦br⟧
